{"word":"H3907 - לָחַשׁ - lâchash - law-khash' - Charmer","slug":"H3907","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לָחַשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lâchash"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>law-khash'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Charmer"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05D7;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - la&#x0302;chash</b> - <i>law-khash'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>whisper</i>; by implication to <i>mumble</i> a spell (as a magician): - charmer, whisper (together)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3873\">H3873</a>, <a href=\"#/H3908\">H3908</a>, <a href=\"#/H3910\">H3910</a>"}]}